gobblin.config.store.api

Annotation Type ConfigStoreWithStableVersioning


  • @Documented
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=TYPE)
 @Alpha
public @interface ConfigStoreWithStableVersioning
    The ConfigStoreWithStableVersioning annotation is used to indicate that the configuration store supports stable versioning. This means that:
    • Once published the version will remain available for at least a day even if it gets rolled back.
    • The version and all its configuration objects are immutable.
    Version stability defines the possible outcomes for repeated calls to ConfigStore.getOwnConfig(ConfigKeyPath, String) for the same config key and version from the same or different JVMs. This is used in conjunction with VersionStabilityPolicy to control client library behavior with respect to caching config values.
